{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01TCP5HJMGz8gXbKf48LzU2z","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# integrate-iam\n2\t\n3\t## Goal\n4\t\n5\tWire lifecycle and authz handlers into a single http.ServeMux and expose it for the platform main.go. Create iam.go (package iam) in the output directory. It must instantiate lifecycle.New() and authz.New(), register their routes on a shared mux (route prefixes: /users and /auth go to lifecycle; /roles, /authz, and /users/ sub-paths for roles go to authz — use pattern matching carefully so /users/{id}/roles routes to authz while /users/{id} routes to lifecycle), and return the mux via a NewMux() function. No port binding here — the platform main.go calls http.ListenAndServe(\":8082\", iam.NewMux()). Task Level: INTERNAL.\n6\t\n7\t## Context\n8\t\n9\t### Level 1 — fbc6d9-0000-build-1\n10\t\n11\t### Level 2 — fbc6d9-0001-iam\n12\tIdentity and access management listener (port 8082) composed of two sub-components — lifecycle (user CRUD and authentication) and authz-rbac (roles and permission checks) — that together handle all ten IAM HTTP endpoints.\n13\t\n14\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f7aca593-a67a-40e6-95f5-6d62c7291aff","uuid":"addeb8f9-cf39-450f-8aae-e1fd368fdc16","timestamp":"2026-04-05T09:22:13.736Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/david/Go/src/github.com/cornjacket/ai-builder/acceptance-spec/sandbox/regressions/platform-monolith/target/project/tasks/main/in-progress/fbc6d9-platform/fbc6d9-0000-build-1/fbc6d9-0001-iam/fbc6d9-0002-integrate-iam/README.md","content":"# integrate-iam\n\n## Goal\n\nWire lifecycle and authz handlers into a single http.ServeMux and expose it for the platform main.go. Create iam.go (package iam) in the output directory. It must instantiate lifecycle.New() and authz.New(), register their routes on a shared mux (route prefixes: /users and /auth go to lifecycle; /roles, /authz, and /users/ sub-paths for roles go to authz — use pattern matching carefully so /users/{id}/roles routes to authz while /users/{id} routes to lifecycle), and return the mux via a NewMux() function. No port binding here — the platform main.go calls http.ListenAndServe(\":8082\", iam.NewMux()). Task Level: INTERNAL.\n\n## Context\n\n### Level 1 — fbc6d9-0000-build-1\n\n### Level 2 — fbc6d9-0001-iam\nIdentity and access management listener (port 8082) composed of two sub-components — lifecycle (user CRUD and authentication) and authz-rbac (roles and permission checks) — that together handle all ten IAM HTTP endpoints.\n\n","numLines":14,"startLine":1,"totalLines":14}}}
